description:
&lt;p&gt;There is a fantastic opportunity for enthusiastic and innovative Health Visitors to join our friendly, supportive team in West London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work with families in one of the most diverse boroughs in London to give children the best possible start in life by providing the most up-to-date evidence based support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our team, you will contribute to the delivery of the national Healthy Child programme across Hounslow, working closely with partners, such as GPs, children’s centres and social care providing seamless care to the population of Hounslow. You’ll also have an important role helping to recognise and protect vulnerable children.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we’ll provide you with a comprehensive package of training and professional development, including regular supervision, weekly practice development sessions, and training in Family Partnership Model and MECSH, an enhanced programme of interventions for vulnerable and at-risk mothers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also provide corporate membership to the iHV, mentorship and an excellent preceptorship package for newly qualified health visitors. We are happy to fund your DBS check as part of our recruitment process&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Looking after you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are committed to staff health and wellbeing - providing staff with an environment and opportunities that encourage and enable them to lead healthy lives and make choices that support their wellbeing e.g. Subsidised Yoga Classes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HRCH was ranked as the&lt;strong&gt; top community trust in England for the number of staff who would recommend it as a place to work &lt;/strong&gt;in the NHS Staff Survey 2017/18.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also have the &lt;strong&gt;highest percentage of colleagues who feel their role makes a difference to patients.&lt;/strong&gt; When you join our team, you’ll have the opportunity to touch people’s lives every day in their own community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hounslow’s diverse population and high level of need makes this an incredibly stimulating and rewarding environment to work in, particularly for someone who has recently qualified. There is no better feeling than knowing you have helped to make a positive difference to someone’s life – and we’d love you to join us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oonagh McGeever Clinical Service Manager 07557 033 358&lt;/p&gt;
